WEBVTT

00:00.190 --> 00:01.539
Bay: <i> Previously on</i> Switched at Birth...

00:02.254 --> 00:03.303
No, you do this now.

00:03.338 --> 00:05.171
It's done. It's forever.

00:05.207 --> 00:06.939
I know that you're stuck in the middle.

00:11.079 --> 00:12.045
Of course.

00:12.080 --> 00:13.763
You gave Melody $50,000?

00:13.799 --> 00:14.814
For the deaf program.

00:14.850 --> 00:16.082
Daphne's tuition is past-due.

00:16.117 --> 00:17.984
I said that I'm taking care of it.

00:18.020 --> 00:20.854
There's nothing left for me to
liquidate. That pretty much taps me out.

00:20.889 --> 00:21.888
I'm pregnant.

00:22.908 --> 00:24.491
I knew there was a higher chance.

00:24.526 --> 00:26.459
I'm sorry. I don't know
what you're talking about.

00:26.495 --> 00:28.495
The baby has Down syndrome.

00:28.497 --> 00:29.562
I don't think we're ready for this.

00:29.598 --> 00:31.598
I know.

00:31.633 --> 00:33.366
My mom, she's still alive.

00:33.435 --> 00:34.834
Her name is Hope Paxton.

00:34.870 --> 00:37.570
<i>She's working at a car shop back
where we used to live in Atlanta.</i>

00:37.642 --> 00:40.242
I did what I had to do to protect my son,

00:40.295 --> 00:41.510
and I'd do it again in a second.

00:41.546 --> 00:43.312
<i>Regina: I wish it wasn't like this.</i>

00:45.383 --> 00:47.049
(Regina laughing)

00:47.101 --> 00:48.351
Nice move.

00:48.353 --> 00:49.885
Hmm. Which one?

00:51.923 --> 00:53.823
Leaving work in the
middle of the afternoon.

00:54.826 --> 00:57.893
Actually, you are the
best move I've ever made.

00:59.931 --> 01:02.698
Well, I can't argue with that.

01:04.635 --> 01:06.736
So are you ready for my next big idea?

01:06.738 --> 01:07.703
Bring it.

01:09.540 --> 01:11.474
I think we should move in together.

01:12.510 --> 01:14.276
- You do?
- Yeah.

01:14.312 --> 01:17.346
Look, for the first time in
years, I feel like I can breathe.

01:17.382 --> 01:20.082
And now that you know everything
there is to know about me,

01:20.118 --> 01:21.984
we can really become a family.

01:23.021 --> 01:24.036
(Exhales)

01:24.088 --> 01:26.038
That's really nice.

01:28.943 --> 01:30.826
You don't have to give
me an answer right now.

01:30.862 --> 01:31.827
Okay.

01:31.863 --> 01:33.896
- Take your time.
- Thank you.

01:33.931 --> 01:36.065
You got an answer yet?

01:36.100 --> 01:37.917
Give me a few days, hmm?

01:37.969 --> 01:40.553
Okay. You got it.

01:41.356 --> 01:42.726
Now, come on. Let's go back and make sure

01:42.727 --> 01:44.250
no one's burned our coffee house down.

01:45.877 --> 01:47.476
Come on.

01:52.650 --> 01:53.716
(Door opening and closing)

01:53.751 --> 01:57.386
Hey, just the man I was looking for.

01:57.438 --> 01:59.155
I found a space.

02:01.292 --> 02:03.042
- A space?
- Yes.

02:03.094 --> 02:04.260
For the musical.

02:04.295 --> 02:06.145
It's got 200 seats,

02:06.197 --> 02:10.066
the acoustics are great, and
the spring slot is available.

02:10.101 --> 02:11.000
Oh.

02:12.220 --> 02:13.302
Exciting, right?

02:16.007 --> 02:16.972
I can't.

02:18.059 --> 02:19.742
Um, I'm out.

02:20.745 --> 02:23.045
- Of what?
- The musical. Um...

02:24.048 --> 02:26.882
I gotta pass. I'm sorry. I...

02:26.918 --> 02:30.719
I just have other things going
on. I just can't right now.

02:30.755 --> 02:33.389
What's going on, honey?

02:37.278 --> 02:38.227
Nothing.

02:39.497 --> 02:40.429
Something.

02:42.567 --> 02:43.566
I can't.

02:47.338 --> 02:48.304
Yes, you can.

02:50.358 --> 02:52.174
Honey, no matter what it is.

03:00.118 --> 03:01.917
Can someone please say something?

03:03.955 --> 03:06.956
I told Toby that we were here for him,

03:06.991 --> 03:09.758
for him and Lily, whatever they need.

03:09.794 --> 03:11.777
Is there a you and Lily?

03:13.364 --> 03:15.331
(Exhales)

03:15.366 --> 03:16.398
I don't know.

03:16.434 --> 03:17.666
I don't know anything.

03:20.304 --> 03:22.271
I just don't understand how this happened.

03:24.275 --> 03:26.041
Did I not teach you to be responsible?

03:27.478 --> 03:28.944
I was responsible.

03:28.980 --> 03:32.014
Come on, John. Sometimes,
these things just happen.

03:32.049 --> 03:35.167
Well, all I'm seeing is him stumbling
from one catastrophe to the next.

03:35.203 --> 03:36.986
- Thanks.
- John!

03:37.989 --> 03:39.922
Do you think I wanted this to happen?

03:39.957 --> 03:41.790
Don't you think I'm trying
to do the right thing?

03:41.826 --> 03:43.926
And what is that, Toby?
What's the right thing?

03:44.912 --> 03:46.662
I don't know.

03:46.697 --> 03:48.481
I don't know what she's gonna do.

03:48.516 --> 03:49.798
I'm trying to support her.

03:49.834 --> 03:52.334
Do you have any idea

03:52.386 --> 03:55.604
how much it costs to take
care of a kid like that?

03:57.208 --> 03:59.108
(Shouts) Do you?

03:59.143 --> 04:01.277
Medical bills, therapists, tutors...

04:01.312 --> 04:04.930
do you have any idea
what all of this means?

04:04.982 --> 04:06.098
I am sure he knows.

04:06.150 --> 04:07.283
You're sure, Kathryn? Are you sure?

04:07.335 --> 04:08.984
Because I am not so sure.

04:09.020 --> 04:10.135
Let me tell you something.

04:10.188 --> 04:12.738
Kids like this may never be on their own,

04:12.790 --> 04:15.791
and that means you are responsible forever.

04:16.994 --> 04:18.827
Now, tell me, who's gonna pay for that?

04:19.829 --> 04:20.930
- (Silently)
- You?

04:20.964 --> 04:22.731
No. No, of course not. No.

04:22.767 --> 04:24.567
Oh, right, because you figure

04:24.602 --> 04:26.635
you can just go on screwing up,

04:26.671 --> 04:29.605
and I'll swoop in and clean up
your mess just like I always do.

04:29.640 --> 04:30.706
Dad with his wallet.

04:30.741 --> 04:31.774
- John!
- Dad.

04:31.809 --> 04:33.375
Not this time!

04:34.362 --> 04:35.578
This time, I won't.

04:43.504 --> 04:46.188
Why did I think it would go any different?

04:46.224 --> 04:47.990
(Door slamming)

04:47.992 --> 04:50.059
Toby, it is a lot to hear.

04:51.062 --> 04:51.994
I know that.

04:53.130 --> 04:54.997
I'll go talk to him.

04:55.032 --> 04:56.749
It'll be okay.

04:59.003 --> 05:00.035
I'm going home.

05:03.841 --> 05:04.807
(Door slamming)

05:06.110 --> 05:09.044
(Theme music playing)

05:09.045 --> 05:13.770
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

05:13.918 --> 05:17.219
I've got some news about Eric.

05:17.221 --> 05:18.220
Everything okay?

05:19.857 --> 05:22.191
He asked me to move in with him and Will.

05:22.226 --> 05:25.027
That's fantastic. I'm so happy for you.

05:25.062 --> 05:27.780
Hold on. I haven't said yes yet.

05:27.815 --> 05:29.064
Why not?

05:29.066 --> 05:32.067
I'm still considering the idea.

05:32.119 --> 05:33.902
And I wanted to know what you thought.

05:35.072 --> 05:36.989
I think I couldn't be happier

05:37.041 --> 05:39.041
you found such an incredible guy.

05:39.076 --> 05:41.744
- You really deserve it.
- Thank you.

05:41.796 --> 05:42.911
- (Phone vibrating)
- Uh... oh!

05:44.832 --> 05:46.248
- Hmm.
- The boyfriend?

05:46.250 --> 05:49.218
Um, your boyfriend actually.

05:49.253 --> 05:50.919
And he's a sore loser.

05:52.139 --> 05:55.758
Um, we've been in an epic
battle on Words with Friends,

05:55.760 --> 05:57.142
and I just won.

05:57.178 --> 05:58.978
I know a lot of "Q" words.

05:59.013 --> 06:01.146
I... I didn't know you were word friends.

06:01.182 --> 06:04.767
Oh, I should make dinner for
the two of you to celebrate.

06:04.819 --> 06:07.770
Well, hold on. I'm still
thinking things through,

06:07.772 --> 06:08.988
and there's nothing to celebrate yet.

06:09.023 --> 06:11.940
Okay, fine. I'll just make dinner.

06:11.942 --> 06:17.079
I'm gonna make all dishes that
start with "Q" just to torment him.

06:17.114 --> 06:18.947
(Laughing) Okay, sure.

06:18.949 --> 06:20.783
- All right. See you soon.
- Okay.

06:23.120 --> 06:26.922
He's a 21-year-old kid,
Kathryn! Come on! 21?

06:26.957 --> 06:28.123
I know.

06:28.125 --> 06:30.843
Raising a mentally-retarded child?

06:30.878 --> 06:32.094
John, walk in to the 21st century.

06:32.129 --> 06:33.929
You say Down syndrome.

06:33.964 --> 06:34.946
Whatever you wanna call it.

06:34.947 --> 06:37.306
It's a kid that's gonna
require extensive medical care,

06:37.318 --> 06:38.851
and that costs money.

06:38.886 --> 06:42.971
I cannot believe that the first thing
you think of is how much it's gonna cost.

06:42.973 --> 06:44.223
This is your grandchild.

06:44.331 --> 06:46.197
He didn't even bring up adoption.

06:46.233 --> 06:48.283
I am sure that there are
tons of people out there

06:48.335 --> 06:50.835
who are better-equipped
to raise a kid like that

06:50.871 --> 06:53.171
than our under-employed,
flip-flop-wearing son.

06:53.206 --> 06:56.091
You seriously want our
grandchild raised by strangers?

06:57.127 --> 07:00.245
May I remind you that, technically,
we are strangers to Bay,

07:00.280 --> 07:02.881
and that a stranger raised our daughter?

07:02.883 --> 07:04.182
Not by choice.

07:04.217 --> 07:07.135
Is this how you imagined spending
our third act, raising a baby?

07:07.187 --> 07:09.104
I don't know about you,
but I am too old for that.

07:09.139 --> 07:11.022
We would help him.

07:11.057 --> 07:12.974
Not raise the baby ourselves.

07:13.026 --> 07:15.226
Uh-huh. Well, you can count me out.

07:15.278 --> 07:17.145
- John.
- I'm going.

07:17.197 --> 07:19.147
Someone around here
has gotta earn a living.

07:20.233 --> 07:21.950
(Door opening and closing)

07:23.904 --> 07:27.205
- Bay: Have you heard?
- Yeah, I found out kind of by accident.

07:27.240 --> 07:29.908
J.K. freaked on him.

07:31.144 --> 07:35.079
Um, I'm sure he'll come around
by the time the baby arrives.

07:35.132 --> 07:36.965
(Scoffs)

07:37.000 --> 07:39.167
You're joking, right?

07:39.219 --> 07:44.055
You think that Toby should
become a parent right now?

07:44.090 --> 07:47.292
Lots of people become parents at his age.

07:47.327 --> 07:50.862
And it ruins their lives.

07:50.897 --> 07:52.964
My mom had me at that age.

07:52.999 --> 07:54.165
She actually had me.

07:54.201 --> 07:56.868
Okay, well, you know what I mean.

07:56.903 --> 07:58.937
Having a baby didn't ruin her life.

07:58.972 --> 08:00.688
(Scoffs)

08:00.724 --> 08:04.709
I'm just saying they have a lot
of options available to them.

08:04.744 --> 08:07.479
In fact, I can think of
two other ones off-hand.

08:08.498 --> 08:09.781
You mean one other option?

08:13.603 --> 08:15.520
Are you telling me that you're pr...

08:17.274 --> 08:19.607
Wow. Okay. Um...

08:21.294 --> 08:24.329
I guess we've never had this conversation.

08:25.398 --> 08:26.364
I guess not.

08:28.051 --> 08:29.067
I'm just surprised.

08:30.070 --> 08:31.269
Why?

08:31.271 --> 08:34.938
I don't eat meat, and I'm
against capital punishment.

08:34.975 --> 08:38.743
What about the whole Chip
Coto abstinence bill thing?

08:38.778 --> 08:41.044
I'm for contraception.

08:41.081 --> 08:45.617
You drove me to get the morning-after pill.

08:45.652 --> 08:47.919
The morning-after pill
is not an abortion pill.

08:47.954 --> 08:50.922
So you think that the
law should be overturned?

08:50.957 --> 08:55.343
No, I just think that we
should value all forms of life.

08:55.378 --> 08:57.428
Wait. I'm sorry. Is this from Regina,

08:57.430 --> 08:58.746
because I for sure thought
that she would be...

08:58.782 --> 09:01.366
She is. My mom and I disagree.

09:04.321 --> 09:05.603
So do my mom and I.

09:12.245 --> 09:14.012
We shouldn't get into this.

09:14.064 --> 09:15.046
You're right.

09:18.885 --> 09:19.801
Anyway...

09:21.221 --> 09:22.787
It's Toby and Lily's decision.

09:23.790 --> 09:24.789
Exactly.

09:24.824 --> 09:28.610
And I just want him to be fully-educated

09:28.662 --> 09:33.731
before he makes a decision that
he has to live with forever.

09:33.733 --> 09:36.834
Well, we can both agree on that.

09:40.574 --> 09:42.423
So, they're...

09:43.426 --> 09:44.375
gonna keep it?

09:45.695 --> 09:46.644
I don't know.

09:48.582 --> 09:51.115
I have my feelings about it,

09:51.151 --> 09:53.184
but Toby hasn't asked my opinion.

09:53.236 --> 09:55.303
Probably because he
knows how I feel about it.

09:55.338 --> 09:58.022
(Exhales) It's a lot to
deal with, no matter what.

09:59.059 --> 10:01.326
Oh, my god. John, he just... he lost it.

10:01.378 --> 10:02.660
I know it's a lot,

10:02.696 --> 10:05.129
but I'm actually afraid he's
gonna have another heart attack.

10:05.165 --> 10:06.080
He...

10:07.100 --> 10:10.034
Does seem to be under
a lot of stress lately.

10:10.070 --> 10:11.269
What do you mean?

10:11.304 --> 10:16.524
Well, I was gonna say something,
but I didn't wanna seem nosy.

10:16.576 --> 10:17.542
What?

10:17.577 --> 10:19.794
Well, Daphne's tuition was due,

10:19.829 --> 10:22.413
and he seemed a little off.

10:23.450 --> 10:24.816
And then his car, and...

10:25.819 --> 10:27.652
He seems sensitive about money lately.

10:27.687 --> 10:29.253
He hasn't said anything to me.

10:30.373 --> 10:32.490
You know, I am probably wrong.

10:32.509 --> 10:34.392
Just forget I even said anything.

10:36.000 --> 10:42.074
